   <td colspan="4" class="content">
    <pre>So, the about.com bar is a joking example. Basically, all it does is provide an
advertisement on top of the site you really want to see:
<a href="http://netforbeginners.about.com/gi/o.htm?zi=1/XJ&amp;zTi=1&amp;sdn=netforbeginners&amp;cdn=compute&amp;tm=8&amp;f=10&amp;su=p284.9.336.ip_p504.1.336.ip_&amp;tt=2&amp;bt=1&amp;bts=0&amp;zu=http%3A//www.cexx.org/adware.htm">http://netforbeginners.about.com/gi/o.htm?zi=1/XJ&amp;zTi=1&amp;sdn=netforbeginners&amp;cdn=compute&amp;tm=8&amp;f=10&amp;su=p284.9.336.ip_p504.1.336.ip_&amp;tt=2&amp;bt=1&amp;bts=0&amp;zu=http%3A//www.cexx.org/adware.htm</a>

But you could imagine, instead of an ad, a button like, "I want to work on this"
or "Take me back to the volunteer opportunity finder".</pre>
   </td>
  </tr>
 
 
